RICHLAND-STRYKER GENERATION LLC REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE
Richland-Stryker Generation LLC (“Richland-Stryker”) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service (“Reactive Service”) from an electric generation facility located outside of Toledo, Ohio (“Facility”) that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (“PJM”). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth Richland-Stryker’s revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the Facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Service.
This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT
The total annual revenue requirement is $700,000.00. The total monthly revenue requirement is $700,000.00 / 12 = $58,333.33
The annual revenue requirement is divided among the seven units that comprise the Facility as follows:
Unit 1 – $24,207.56
Unit 2 – $24,207.56
Unit 3 – $24,207.56
Unit 4 – $198,906.11
Unit 5 – $198,906.11
Unit 6 – $198,906.11
Stryker – $30,658.98
